  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [x] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (8e365be 2023-07-18T00:28:12.648082999Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test -vvvv\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen I want to simulate an on-chain tx locally: https://explorer.phalcon.xyz/tx/eth/0x2ff65b4c1bae6f7e18da38a9e155c2090276034e4693ac455f7c2550f0b8573a\r\nI simply createSelectFork, prank the msg.sender, and call the same contract with the same raw data:\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction setUp() public {\r\n        vm.createSelectFork(\"eth\", 17718830);\r\n        // omitted\r\n    }\r\nfunction test1C09() public {\r\n        //...omitted\r\n        address bot = 0xD7f3FBe8C72a961A5515203eADA59750437Fa762;\r\n        vm.startPrank(0x1C09A10047fcc944efDE9226e259edDfde2c1cF0);\r\n        bytes memory a = hex\"0000000600000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000b5cf37f793f85139c0000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000005c8d019d380000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000064b6489c\";\r\n        bot.call(a);\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe local test show the gas:\r\n![image](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/assets/38470282/b38b6b61-8e69-4251-b385-61d2af2041a2)\r\nWhile the on-chain real gas is: (from above phalcon gas profiler)\r\n![image](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/assets/38470282/f7b632d6-8f11-4ce5-98fe-894c2000d379)\r\n![image](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/assets/38470282/28f8e056-15c5-4c97-9838-89573f432baf)\r\n\r\nEven 6000 gas difference in a single token transfer\r\n\r\nSo where does the difference come from? And what should I do to have accurate local gas test?\r\n",
